(605, 1, '2017-08-15 23:22:00', '2017-08-15 23:22:00', '[et_pb_section bb_built="1" _builder_version="3.0.62" custom_padding="2em|||" custom_padding_tablet="0px|||" custom_padding_last_edited="on|phone"][et_pb_row _builder_version="3.0.62" make_fullwidth="on"][et_pb_column type="4_4"][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.0.62" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left" border_style="solid"]\r\n\r\nWith the growing concern around fraudulent works and unauthorized copying of artwork in today''s digital world, many artists have started issuing Certificates of Authenticity (COA). Peter Phillips is now issuing COA’s for any original work of art that he created.&nbsp;\r\nIf you are a museum, gallery or collector, we highly encourage you to request a COA for your Peter Phillips work. To do so, please contact the Phillips family at info@peterphillips.com.\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.0.62" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left" border_style="solid"]\r\n<h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong>WARNING</strong></h1>\r\n[/et_pb_text][et_pb_text _builder_version="3.0.62" background_layout="light" text_orientation="left" border_style="solid"]\r\n\r\nIt has been brought to Mr. Phillips’ attention that there are works in existance, circulating in Switzerland, falsely claiming to be Peter Phillips originals. Should you come across any of the following works claiming to be originals, please contact the Phillips family and/or your local authorities.\r\n\r\nThe following works* are not originals. THEY ARE NOT CONCEPTUALIZED, DESIGNED, PAINTED, CREATED OR AUTORIZED FOR SALE BY THE ARTIST PETER PHILLIPS.\r\n<em>*Photos below are poor in quality and may not depict actual color or full design or works in question.</em>\r\n\r\n[/et_pb_text][/et_pb_column][/et_pb_row][et_pb_row _builder_version="3.0.62" background_position_1="top_left" background_repeat_1="no-repeat" custom_margin="2em|||" custom_margin_tablet="1em|||" custom_margin_last_edited="on|desktop"